adimir Nabokov





TO: JOHN FISCHER

CC, 1 p.





802 East Seneca Street

Ithaca, N.Y.

20 July 1950

Dear Mr. Fischer,

Thanks for your two kind letters. Am enclosing the copy. Good, accurate work on the part of the copy editor.

Re the subtitle. The addition "of a vanished era" will not do at all. The book is not about an era, but about a person, and in that sense the past cannot be said to have "vanished". If you have any other suggestions for a subtitle, let me know. I am completely out of